# Rock–Paper–Scissors Image Classification (TensorFlow / Keras)

A compact Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) for classifying images of hand gestures into **rock**, **paper**, and **scissors**.  
The project loads images from a ZIP file, builds a TensorFlow `tf.data` pipeline, trains a CNN with early stopping, and visualizes misclassified examples.

## Features
- Automatic data extraction  
- tf.data input pipeline  
- Compact CNN model  
- Early stopping & best-model saving  
- Evaluation & error analysis  
- Notebook & script  

## Project Structure
- main.ipynb  
- main.pyt  
- data/archive.zip  
- data/rps_data/  

## Requirements
Python 3.10+, TensorFlow, NumPy, Matplotlib  

## How to Run
Use the notebook or run:  
`python main.pyt`

## Model & Training
CNN with Conv2D, MaxPooling, Dense, Softmax over 3 classes.

## Improvements
Data augmentation, transfer learning, TensorBoard, deployment ideas.

